Description:
Holotype
incomplete, 69 segments, 
78mm
long, thorax 
48mm
long, 
4mm
wide (
Figs 24A,B
). Upper lip long, rounded, margins folded externally. Lower lip flat, wide, slightly swollen. Tentacular membrane with thick swollen edge (
Fig. 24C
); eyespots absent. Few tentacles long, with whitish dorsal and longitudinal waved line (opposite to longitudinal groove) (
Fig. 24E
). First segment elongate laterally, without ventral shield. Twenty four ventral shields; anterior most shields thinner, becoming swollen and wider. Last shields poorly developed. Ventral groove dividing first ventral shields up to end of specimen. Three pairs of branchiae, with thin filaments, decreasing in size and number, and emerging from a swollen base, wider on first pair of branchiae (
Figs 24C,D
). First pair of branchiae with 32 filaments at each side, second pair with 25 filaments on each side, and third pair with 20 filaments on each side. Nephridial papillae not seen. Notopodial glandular tissue pale or whitish, dorsally and ventrally to notopodia along first thoracic half. Anterior most notopodia well-developed; 46 pairs of notopodia; notochaetae of two lengths (
Fig. 24F
), lanceolate, symmetrically bilimbate, with longitudinal striations (
Figs 24G,H
). Pairs of neuropodia swollen, wider on anterior region, smaller on abdomen. Thoracic and abdominal uncini (
Fig. 24I
) with dental formula MF:2; PP and PF absent; Oc slightly convex; Cp with two teeth, as long as two third the MF; Sr narrow; SrP as square button close to a rounded AP; SrA absent; AF absent; Bs slightly curved. Pygidium missing.

Staining pattern:
First ventral shield on segment 2 and notopodial glandular tissue stain deeply (
Fig. 24B
). The remaining ventral shields stain lighter (
Fig. 24B
). Other structures not stained.
